Package org.opengis.wrapper.proj4

Class PJFactory

  • Object
    • PJFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Factory
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PJFactory.EPSG, PJFactory.Objects, PJFactory.Operation, PJFactory.Transform
    public class PJFactory
extends Object
implements Factory
    The base class for factories of Proj.4 wrappers. This base class provides static methods working directly with the Proj.4 definition strings. Subclasses provides implementation of GeoAPI factory interfaces.
    Since:
    3.1

      • createIdentifier

        public static ReferenceIdentifier createIdentifier​(Map<String,​?> properties)
        Creates a simple identifier from the given properties. The full set of properties is documented in the ObjectFactory class. However this implementation uses only the following properties:
        Recognized properties
        Property name Value type Value given to
        "name" Identifier or String IdentifiedObject.getName()
        "codespace" String Identifier.getCodeSpace() on the name
        Parameters:
        properties - the properties, or null if none.
        Returns:
        a reference identifier for the given code space and code, or null.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if any of the requested value is an empty string.

      • createIdentifier

        public static ReferenceIdentifier createIdentifier​(String codespace,
                                                   String code)
        Creates a simple identifier from the given code and codespace. Identifiers are code under the control of some authority (the code space). For example a widely used identifier is EPSG:4326.

        In principle, every ISO 19111 compliant identified object must have an identifier. However this proj4 package is not strict about that. Users are nevertheless encouraged to use this method for creating an identifier before to invoke the other static methods in this PJFactory class.

        Parameters:
        codespace - the code space (for example "EPSG"), or null if none.
        code - the code, for example "4326".
        Returns:
        a reference identifier for the given code space and code.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the code argument is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if any of the given argument is an empty string.

      • createCRS

        public static CoordinateReferenceSystem createCRS​(ReferenceIdentifier crsId,
                                                  ReferenceIdentifier datumId,
                                                  String definition,
                                                  int dimension)
                                           throws IllegalArgumentException
        Creates a new CRS from the given Proj.4 definition string. The CRS can have an arbitrary number of dimensions in the [2-100] range. However Proj.4 will handle at most the 3 first dimensions. All supplemental dimensions will be simply copied unchanged by MathTransform implementations.
        Parameters:
        crsId - the name of the CRS to create, or null if none.
        datumId - the name of the datum to create, or null if none.
        definition - the Proj.4 definition string.
        dimension - the number of dimension of the CRS to create.
        Returns:
        a CRS created from the given definition string and number of dimensions.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the definition string is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if one of the given argument has an invalid value.

      • createOperation

        public static CoordinateOperation createOperation​(ReferenceIdentifier identifier,
                                                  CoordinateReferenceSystem sourceCRS,
                                                  CoordinateReferenceSystem targetCRS)
                                           throws ClassCastException
        Creates an operation for conversion or transformation between two coordinate reference systems. This given source and target CRS must be instances created by this factory.
        Parameters:
        identifier - the name of the operation to create, or null if none.
        sourceCRS - the source coordinate reference system.
        targetCRS - the target coordinate reference system.
        Returns:
        a coordinate operation for transforming coordinates from the given source CRS to the given target CRS.
        Throws:
        ClassCastException - if the given CRS are not instances created by this class.
